latestIgtvVideos.title: How I get Frizz-less Curls 💥
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I've always loved styling my hair with a curling wand more than a straightener only because it gets rid of my frizz & makes it look super voluminous.
Straightener curls don't stay for too long on my hair & definitely look super frizzy after an hour or so!

Also never been a fan of tight curls, so I use the 28mm wand from Ikonic ( You can get it at any beauty store/ amazon) 

Always use my @kerastase_official anti-frizz heat protectant from their Discipline range. (Any will do) 

& used Berina Gold hair spray (Any will do) 

Hope this helps! 
It's been my Go-to hair style, be it for dinners or even weddings

Spray your entire hair with a good hold hair spray if you're going for a wedding though! 
If not, I refrain from spraying on a normal day! 

#CurlyHair #TameFrizz #HairStyling 
#FrizzyHair

latestIgtvVideos.title: Skin Care Routine (Night) ❤
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I'm so so so excited to share this with you'll ❤ 

I hope my skin care routine works for you in some way! 
I've tried a ton of acne serums, ointments & creams & after so many years I've finally stuck to these that have genuinely worked in keeping my skin clear & acne free. 

& don't forget, we all have days when our face is filled with acne & when you feel lost, I just want you to remember that you'll be fine, your skin will be clear, just give it time & don't stress! Because stress aggravates acne & that's the last thing you want. Do not get any acne medication unless you have uncontrollable acne. 

I also try having 3-4 litters of water per day. 
Don't forgot to stay hydrated! 

Going to be sharing another amazing mask I got my hands on in the next video! 

Products used in this video : 

• Neutrogena Oil Free Acne Wash
• The Ordinary Glycolic Toner 7% / Pixi Glow on Nykaa is a 7% too, just a little more expensive than The Ordinary one. 
• The Ordinary : Niacinamide Serum / MamaEarth Skin Correcting Face Serum 
• Himalaya Diaper Rash Cream 
• Lacto Calamine Lotion (Purple Cap for Oily Skin) 
• Femcinol Gel (find it at any chemist) it has Nicotinamide (other name for Niacinamide) which is Vitamin B3, known to cure acne. 
• The Ordinary Peptide Hair Serum for thickening 
• Nivea Lip Balm 
• Glam Glow Face Mask (Super Mud Clearing Treatment) / Any mud mask, I'm currently trying one by Devicaa's (Mrittika Lep) going to give an update on this one soon. 

Thank you & happy skincare to you ☺️

#Niacinamide #TheOrdinary #SkinCareRoutine #SkinCare #OilySkin #CombinationSkin #AcneProneSkin #Acne #NightRoutine

latestIgtvVideos.title: Skin Care Routine (Day) ♥️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I'm so excited to share this with you'll. 
I get so many compliments for my skin & I just had to reveal that skin care is no rocket science once you know what works for you & how little you need to care for it! 

I have combination - mostly oily & acne prone skin! 

The more you do, the more you stress your skin & this is something I've learned in the past few years. 

So the rule is to keep it simple & to point. 

But really I do concentrate on my night care more than my day care routine! 
There are also a bunch of home remedies that I try in between sticking to my routine, will be sharing those as well. 
But you'll know my 'Go- to' face mask, the Multani Mitti & Listerine one! (My 1st IGTV) 

Products I use & some Indian brands that you can try instead of 'The Ordinary' 

• Neutrogena Oil Free Acne Wash 
• Ayur Astringent 
• Neutrogena Oil Free Moisturizer 
• I switch to the Neutrogena Ultra Sheer Dry Touch Sunscreen with SPF 50 if I'm stepping out! 
• The Ordinary Vitamin C serum (Ascorbic 8%, Alpha Arbutin 2%) / You can try the MamaEarth Vitamin C & Turmeric Skin Illuminate Face Serum instead. 
• Lotus White Glow Oatmeal & Yogurt Face Scrub (Physical Exfoliant) 
• The Ordinary Peeling Solution (Chemical Exfoliant) / No chemical exfoliant is as good as this one in this price range. Please tell me if you'll come across any. 
• Olivia Herbal Bleach 

Going to be sharing a secret in my Night Care Routine though (don't judge me for this one 😝) 

Stay Tuned lovelies 🖤

#SkinCare #SkinCareRoutine #Skin #TheOrdinary #CombinationSkin #OilySkin #AcneProneSkin

latestIgtvVideos.title: Glowy Make Up ❤ (Day Series)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So I don't do all the steps everyday of course, but only when I'm going for an event or a fancy day out is when I prefer doing all the steps! 
Always believe in 'Less Is More' so try looking as natural & just sharpen your features instead of faking them! 
On a daily basis its just tone, moisturize, lip & cheek tint! 
Tips to remember : 
1. Opening the eyes is the main thing, use the white pencil & highlight dark areas to give it a lift! 
2. Avoid applying concealer on the upper lid, it creases in the heat/ day 
3. Powder for the eyebrows so you can't see lines drawn on them in the sunlight 
4. SPF, Setting Spray & a good pressed powder are a must have for the day make up routine 
Products used 
1. Ordinary @deciem - Glycolic Acid Toner 
2. Neutrogena SPF moisturizer mixed with MAC strobe cream in Pinklite 
3. Essence Pink color corrector 
4. NYX HD Studio Photogenic Concealer in shade CW 04
5. @benefitindia Hoola Bronzer 
6. @smashboxindia Blush & Highlight Palette - Cali Kissed 
7. @bollyglow Eyeliner - Haute Chocolate 
8. NYX Wonder Pencil - Light 
9. @maccosmeticsindia 3D Black Lash Mascara
10. Smash Box Setting Spray 
11. MAC Skin Finish Powder - Medium
